<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38164a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38164a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38164a"> 164(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ra&apos;s court <font color="green">[in]</font> / dawn</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>The Judgment of Ra was held at sunrise</mark>, and the wicked were thrown into deep pits filled with fire, and their bodies, souls, shadows and hearts were consumed forthwith. The Judgment of Osiris took place near Abydos, probably at midnight, and a decree of swift annihilation was passed by him on the damned. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 21</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
